official documentation of Robot Framework :- https://robotframework.org/#resources
tutorial : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qnA2P3VBkeA&list=PLL34mf651faORDOyJrk0E6k9FM-wKgfPV&index=2

Steps to download Robot Framework :-
- Download .jar file from path https://github.com/lte2000/intellibot/blob/master/intellibot.jar
- [Go to setting] > [plugins] > [(gear)] > [download plugin from disk > select the .jar file] > restart ide
- install pip install robotframework
- check if robotframework installed via [robot --version]
- download selenium browserdrivers for the browser

For adding path of executable files in the .bash file of mac or .zprofile :
cd homedir
vi .bash_profile
for saving file :wq!
to see the path echo $PATH

take executable and add it to c > python > scripts

Every Robot framework file have 4 section :
[ctrl + space] - to have these under written things appear
Every robot file have these 4 sections
*** Settings ***
section dedicated to import, library
[Library] :-
 - to use any Library from robot framework we need to install the library first
 - pip install robotframework-libraryName

*** Variables ***
There are 4 type of variables:
1. scaler variable
2. dictionary variable
3. list variable

about keywords and test cases - https://robotframework.org/SeleniumLibrary/
selenium keywords documentation - https://robotframework.org/SeleniumLibrary/SeleniumLibrary.html
*** Keywords ***
*** Test Cases ***
----------------------------------------------------------------------ROBOT FRAMEWORK--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ctr + space >>>>>  underwritten 4 sections will appear to write in .robot file
{*** Settings ***}
{*** Keywords ***}
{*** Variables ***}
{*** test cases ***}

to run the .robot file from cmd :--
{robot .\name_of_file / robot .\{initials of letter and then press tab}]}
{robot -v variable_name:variable_value .\{initials of letter and then press tab}]}
{robot -d folder_name_where_logs_stay .\.robot_file} - this would add the log files to this folder not in the root

To have executables with the robot framework we need to paste the .exe file in scripts in python39


path of file always with :-
1. single forward slash
2. double backward slash
 ex: C:\\Users\\User\\Desktop\\responsive_issue.png
 ex: C:/Users/User/Desktop/responsive_issue.png

